        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Saint Thomas W. I</placeName>
                <add>?</add>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Tamaz 5622 July 6/62</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd. I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Reverend &amp; Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Being in possession of your<lb/> esteemed favour of <date>May 29<hi
                        rend="sup">th</hi></date> I avail myself of<lb/> this opportunity to reply
                thereto, and likewise to<lb/> convey the united thanks of <persName>Mrs.
                    Myers</persName> and myself<lb/> for the very kind sentiments and wishes on the
                occasion<lb/> of our happy union, and which are contained in<lb/> your esteemed
                communication. Rest assured<lb/> Revd and Dear Sir that I fully appreciate such<lb/>
                honor at your hands, and that your kind &amp;<lb/> distinguished patronage can but
                lend to stimulate<lb/> me in my humble exertions towards the cause<lb/> of our holy
                faith, and thereby allow me to<lb/> prove myself worthy of the kind
                consideration<lb/> bestowed upon me. I also take this oppor=<lb/>=tunity of most
                sincerely thanking you (Dr Sir)<lb/> for the kind notices which you have been<lb/>
                pleased to take of my humble exertions; and<lb/> which have appeared in your
                valuable periodical,<lb/> and the only fear and regret that I entertain,<lb/> is,
                that in such instances you may have<lb/> been induced to overrate my feeble
                abilities<lb/> and exertions: for I assure you Revd Sir that<lb/> whatever steps I
                take for advocating the truths of</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>our holy religion <del>is</del> are not based upon my own<lb/> abilities but on the
                advice “<add>במקום שאין אנשים השתדל להיות איש</add>”<lb/> I have Dr Sir to beg your
                excuse for being so<lb/> long neglectful in opening our correspondence,<lb/>
                although I have for the last twelve months<lb/> so often projected so to do, and
                from time to<lb/> time been prevented accomplishing my desire,<lb/> but, I trust
                that you will pardon the delay,<lb/> and now that the commencement has taken<lb/>
                place, that it may continue uninterrupted;<lb/> for, I assure you that it will a
                source of<lb/> great <sic>satisficion</sic> and delight to me, to have<lb/> the
                honor of your correspondence, and also of replying<lb/> thereto.</p>
            <p>I thank you sincerely for your kind advice, and<lb/> assure you that I shall never
                become weary<lb/> of my work in the vineyard of the Eternal; nor,<lb/> do I allow
                occasional ingratitude to dampen<lb/> my exertions; for we must in every flock<lb/>
                expect to find some few <hi rend="underline">silly sheep</hi> who <hi
                    rend="underline">will</hi><lb/> wander away form the shepherd, however
                carefully<lb/> he may watch their movements. However, <add>?</add><lb/> I have but a
                few such sheepish heads in my<lb/> flock. You are already made aware that<lb/> in
                the month of <date>January</date> I paid a visit to the<lb/>
                <placeName>Island of Curacoa</placeName>, and it is gratifying for me to<lb/> inform
                you, that I have just received a<lb/> very handsome testimonial from the
                community<lb/> there, in the shape of a <add>?</add> of <del>a</del> very handsome,
                silver</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>goblets with stands to match, each one bearing<lb/> the inscription of its being
                presented to me by my<lb/> coreligionists and admirers <del>of</del> at
                    <placeName>Curacoa</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have not at present any particular<lb/> news to communicate. With
                most sincere &amp;<lb/> best wishes, and assurances of my high regard</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Reverend &amp; Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Yours very faithfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">Myer H. Myers</persName>
            </p>
            <p>P. S.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You would greatly oblige me if at your<lb/> earliest convenience you
                would by the very<lb/> first opportunity supply me with a copy<lb/> of the
                regulations of the <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> Heb<lb/> Sunday School; and
                also 6 copies of<lb/> the most suitable book, the contents of<lb/> which you deem
                that candidates for<lb/> confirmation in our Holy faith should be<lb/> acquainted
                with.</p>
